    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for one three-player source Game.update() where two forced wall deaths leave avatar 1 as the sole round-end survivor, then the source frame loop continues through warmdown.",
      "The harness starts a real source round, waits for delayed PrintManager.start timers, forces avatars 3 and 2 into same-frame wall deaths while avatar 1 survives the terminal update, then advances the 5000 ms warmdown.",
      "The original JS frame loop moves avatar 1 during warmdown; avatar 1 hits the wall at 4150 ms, then source still emits game:stop and the next round:new at 8000 ms because max_score is not reached.",
      "Bonuses are disabled so the pinned random stream contains spawn and PrintManager distances only."
    ]
  },
